  • Method Details

    • search

      public D search(K key)
      Returns the data stored in the first node in the AVL Tree matching key; Cost: O(logn)

      Search on a binary tree with a logarithmic height relative to the number of nodes.

      • Worst/Average-case cost: Θ(logn)
      • Best-case cost: O(1)
      Specified by:
      search in interface Tree<K extends Comparable<K>, D>
      Overrides:
      search in class BinarySearchTree<K extends Comparable<K>, D>
      Parameters:
      key - key value to search
      Returns:
      the data mapped to key or null if key is not in the tree

    • insert

      public void insert(K key, D data) throws IllegalStateException
      Inserts a node storing the mapping (key,data) into the AVL tree; Cost: Θ(logn)

      Null key values are not allowed, while null data values are allowed. Rebalances the AVL Tree, if necessary, to maintain a logarithmic height.

      Specified by:
      insert in interface Tree<K extends Comparable<K>, D>
      Overrides:
      insert in class BinarySearchTree<K extends Comparable<K>, D>
      Parameters:
      key - key value
      data - data associated to the key value
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if the key paramenter is null
